30static const float MAX_AVG_VARIANCE = 0.38f;
31static const float MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE = 0.5f;
32
33static const int W = 3; // Pixel width of a 3x wide line
34static const int w = 2; // Pixel width of a 2x wide line
35static const int N = 1; // Pixed width of a narrow line
36
37/** Valid ITF lengths. Anything longer than the largest value is also allowed. */
38static const std::array<int, 5> DEFAULT_ALLOWED_LENGTHS = { 6, 8, 10, 12, 14 };
39
40/**
41* Start/end guard pattern.
42*
43* Note: The end pattern is reversed because the row is reversed before
44* searching for the END_PATTERN
45*/
46static const std::array<int, 4> START_PATTERN = { N, N, N, N };
47static const std::array<std::array<int, 3>, 2> END_PATTERN_REVERSED = {
48 N, N, w, // 2x
49 N, N, W, // 3x
50};
51
52/**
53* Patterns of Wide / Narrow lines to indicate each digit
54*/
55static const std::array<std::array<int, 5>, 20> PATTERNS = {
56 N, N, w, w, N, // 0
57 w, N, N, N, w, // 1
58 N, w, N, N, w, // 2
59 w, w, N, N, N, // 3
60 N, N, w, N, w, // 4
61 w, N, w, N, N, // 5
62 N, w, w, N, N, // 6
63 N, N, N, w, w, // 7
64 w, N, N, w, N, // 8
65 N, w, N, w, N, // 9
66
67 N, N, W, W, N, // 0
68 W, N, N, N, W, // 1
69 N, W, N, N, W, // 2
70 W, W, N, N, N, // 3
71 N, N, W, N, W, // 4
72 W, N, W, N, N, // 5
73 N, W, W, N, N, // 6
74 N, N, N, W, W, // 7
75 W, N, N, W, N, // 8
76 N, W, N, W, N, // 9
77};
78
79/**
80* @param row row of black/white values to search
81* @param payloadStart offset of start pattern
82* @param resultString {@link StringBuilder} to append decoded chars to
83* @throws NotFoundException if decoding could not complete successfully
84*/
85static std::string DecodeMiddle(BitArray::Iterator begin, BitArray::Iterator end)
86{
87 std::string resultString;
88 resultString.reserve(20);
89
90 // Digits are interleaved in pairs - 5 black lines for one digit, and the 5
91 // interleaved white lines for the second digit.
92 // Therefore, need to scan 10 lines and then
93 // split these into two arrays
94 std::array<int, 10> counterDigitPair = {};
95 std::array<int, 5> counterBlack = {};
96 std::array<int, 5> counterWhite = {};
97
98 while (begin != end) {
99
100 // Get 10 runs of black/white.
101 auto range = RowReader::RecordPattern(begin, end, counterDigitPair);
102 if (!range)
103 return {};
104
105 // Split them into each array
106 for (int k = 0; k < 5; k++) {
107 counterBlack[k] = counterDigitPair[2 * k];
108 counterWhite[k] = counterDigitPair[2 * k + 1];
109 }
110
111 int bestMatch = RowReader::DecodeDigit(counterBlack, PATTERNS, MAX_AVG_VARIANCE, MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE);
112 if (bestMatch == -1)
113 return {};
114
115 resultString.push_back((char)('0' + bestMatch % 10));
116
117 bestMatch = RowReader::DecodeDigit(counterWhite, PATTERNS, MAX_AVG_VARIANCE, MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE);
118 if (bestMatch == -1)
119 return {};
120
121 resultString.push_back((char)('0' + bestMatch % 10));
122
123 begin = range.end;
124 }
125 return resultString;
126}
127
128/**
129* @param row row of black/white values to search
130* @param pattern pattern of counts of number of black and white pixels that are
131* being searched for as a pattern
132* @return start/end horizontal offset of guard pattern, as an array of two
133* ints
134* @throws NotFoundException if pattern is not found
135*/
136template <typename Container>
137static BitArray::Range
138FindGuardPattern(const BitArray& row, const Container& pattern)
139{
140 Container counters = {};
141 auto pat_sum = Reduce(pattern);
142
143 return RowReader::FindPattern(
144 row.getNextSet(row.begin()), row.end(), counters,
145 [&row, &pattern, pat_sum](BitArray::Iterator begin, BitArray::Iterator end, const Container& counters) {
146 // The start & end patterns must be pre/post fixed by a quiet zone. This
147 // zone must be at least 10 times the width of a narrow line. Scan back until
148 // we either get to the start of the barcode or match the necessary number of
149 // quiet zone pixels.
150 // ref: http://www.barcode-1.net/i25code.html
151
152 // Determine the width of a narrow line in pixels. See definition of START and END patterns above
153 int quietZoneWidth = 10 * static_cast<int>(end - begin) / pat_sum; // 10 * narrowLineWidth;
154 return row.hasQuiteZone(begin, -quietZoneWidth) &&
155 RowReader::PatternMatchVariance(counters, pattern, MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE) < MAX_AVG_VARIANCE;
156 });
157}
158
159/**
160* Identify where the start of the middle / payload section starts.
161*
162* @param row row of black/white values to search
163* @return Array, containing index of start of 'start block' and end of
164* 'start block'
165* @throws NotFoundException
166*/
167static BitArray::Range DecodeStart(const BitArray& row)
168{
169 return FindGuardPattern(row, START_PATTERN);
170}
171
172/**
173* Identify where the end of the middle / payload section ends.
174*
175* @param row row of black/white values to search
176* @return Array, containing index of start of 'end block' and end of 'end
177* block'
178* @throws NotFoundException
179*/
180static BitArray::Range DecodeEnd(const BitArray& row)
181{
182 BitArray revRow = row.copy();
183 // For convenience, reverse the row and then
184 // search from 'the start' for the end block
185 revRow.reverse();
186 auto range = FindGuardPattern(revRow, END_PATTERN_REVERSED[0]);
187 if (!range)
188 range = FindGuardPattern(revRow, END_PATTERN_REVERSED[1]);
189
190 // Now recalculate the indices of where the 'endblock' starts & stops to accommodate
191 // the reversed nature of the search
192 auto rowSize = Size(row);
193 return {row.iterAt(rowSize - static_cast<int>(range.end - revRow.begin())),
194 row.iterAt(rowSize - static_cast<int>(range.begin - revRow.begin()))};
195}
196
197ITFReader::ITFReader(const DecodeHints& hints) :
198 _allowedLengths(hints.allowedLengths())
199{
200 if (_allowedLengths.empty()) {
201 _allowedLengths.assign(DEFAULT_ALLOWED_LENGTHS.begin(), DEFAULT_ALLOWED_LENGTHS.end());
202 }
203}
204
205Result
206ITFReader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>&) const
207{
208 // Find out where the Middle section (payload) starts & ends
209 auto startRange = DecodeStart(row);
210 if (!startRange)
211 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
212
213 auto endRange = DecodeEnd(row);
214 if (!endRange || !(startRange.end < endRange.begin))
215 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
216
217 std::string result = DecodeMiddle(startRange.end, endRange.begin);
218 if (result.empty())
219 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
220
221 // To avoid false positives with 2D barcodes (and other patterns), make
222 // an assumption that the decoded string must be a 'standard' length if it's short
223 int length = Size(result);
224 if (!_allowedLengths.empty() && !Contains(_allowedLengths, length)) {
225 int maxAllowedLength = *std::max_element(_allowedLengths.begin(), _allowedLengths.end());
226 if (length < maxAllowedLength)
227 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
228 }
229
230 int xStart = static_cast<int>(startRange.begin - row.begin());
231 int xStop = static_cast<int>(endRange.end - row.begin() - 1);
232 return Result(result, rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::ITF);
233}
234
235constexpr auto START_PATTERN_ = FixedPattern<4, 4>{1, 1, 1, 1};
236constexpr auto STOP_PATTERN_1 = FixedPattern<3, 4>{2, 1, 1};
237constexpr auto STOP_PATTERN_2 = FixedPattern<3, 5>{3, 1, 1};
238
239constexpr float QUITE_ZONE_SCALE = 2.5; // spec says 10 modules
240
241Result ITFReader::decodePattern(int rowNumber, const PatternView& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>&) const
242{
243 const int minCharCount = 6;
244
245 auto next = ZXing::FindPattern(row.subView(0, -(4 + minCharCount/2 + 3)), START_PATTERN_, QUITE_ZONE_SCALE);
246 if (!next.isValid())
247 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
248
249 std::string txt;
250 txt.reserve(20);
251
252 constexpr int weights[] = {1, 2, 4, 7, 0};
253 int xStart = next.pixelsInFront();
254 next = next.subView(4, 10);
255
256 while (next.index() < row.size() - (10 + 3)) {
257 const auto threshold = NarrowWideThreshold(next);
258 if (!threshold.isValid())
259 break;
260
261 BarAndSpace<int> digits, numWide;
262 for (int i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
263 if (next[i] > threshold[i] * 2)
264 break;
265 numWide[i] += next[i] > threshold[i];
266 digits[i] += weights[i/2] * (next[i] > threshold[i]);
267 }
268
269 if (numWide.bar != 2 || numWide.space != 2)
270 break;
271
272 for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i)
273 txt.push_back((char)('0' + (digits[i] == 11 ? 0 : digits[i])));
274
275 next.skipSymbol();
276 }
277
278 next = next.subView(0, 3);
279
280 if (Size(txt) < minCharCount || !next.hasQuiteZoneAfter(QUITE_ZONE_SCALE))
281 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
282
283 if (!IsPattern(next, STOP_PATTERN_1) && !IsPattern(next, STOP_PATTERN_2))
284 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
285
286 int xStop = next.pixelsInFront() + next.size() - 1;
287 return Result(txt, rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::ITF);
288}
